The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 At Rs 17 crore, Pfizer net profit stays flat

 Mumbai, Jan. 20 (PTI): Pfizer today recorded a net profit of Rs 17 crore in the quarter ended November 30, 2006, registering a slight dip of 2.13 per cent compared with Rs 17.37 crore a year ago.

 Total income (net of excise and sales tax) of the company for the fourth quarter, however, rose to Rs 182.86 crore, recording an increase of 1.69 per cent compared with Rs 179.82 crore in the previous fiscal, Pfizer informed BSE.

 The company has also recommended a dividend of Rs 2.50 (125 per cent) per equity share of Rs 10 for the year ended November 30.

 The group has posted a net profit of Rs 106.33 crore in the year compared with Rs 70.73 crore a year ago.

 Consolidated total income of the group (net of excise and sales tax) has increased to Rs 726.26 crore in the quarter from Rs 644.09 crore.

 For the year ended November 30, Pfizer Ltds net profit was Rs 105.73 crore against Rs 68.12 crore in the previous year.

 Total income (net of excise and sales tax) increased to Rs 721.75 crore against Rs 639.55 crore a year ago. 

 Bharat Forge

 Auto component manufacturer Bharat Forge today clocked an 18.23 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 62.97 crore in the quarter ended December 31 against Rs 53.26 crore recorded in the year-ago period.

 Total income (net of excise) of the Pune-based company also witnessed a similar increase of 18.74 per cent to Rs 493.31 crore in the quarter from Rs 415.45 crore posted in the corresponding quarter of the previous year, Bharat Forge informed the BSE.

 The consolidated results of the group show that it has posted a net profit of Rs 76.95 crore for the quarter compared with Rs 62.69 crore a year ago.

 The groups consolidated total income (net of excise) has also increased to Rs 1037.09 crore in the quarter against Rs 956.67 crore in the year-ago period. 

 Godrej Consumer 

 Godrej Consumer Products today posted a marginal increase in net profit to Rs 36.63 crore in the quarter ended December 31 from Rs 36.12 crore in the same quarter last year. 

 Total income (net of excise) increased 16.19 per cent to Rs 199.91 crore for the quarter from Rs 172.04 crore a year ago .

 The board has declared a third interim dividend of Re 1 on shares of Re 1 each (100 per cent) for 2006-07. 

 The group posted a net profit of Rs 39.56 crore in the quarter, compared with Rs 35.77 crore. Total income of the group (net of excise) increased to Rs 239.73 crore against Rs 187.15 crore a year ago.




